text: Jacques Senard (21 November 1919 – 22 September 2020) was a French politician. He was born in Corgoloin, France. He was the French Ambassador to the Netherlands between 1972 to 1976 and to Egypt between 1976 to 1979. Senard died on 22 September 2020 in Arles, France at the age of 100. ==References== Category:1919 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Ambassadors of France Category:French centenarians Category:People from Côte-d'Or Category:Politicians from Bourgogne-Franche-Comté
